Edward Ramon,<br><br>
No need to apologize for telling of your accomplishments. I am very very proud of you.<br><br>
A few years ago, Senator Bob Kerry of Nebraska - a Congressional Medal of Honor winner - spoke of how someday Vietnam Veterans would begin to talk of these achievements - medals and such. That time is now.<br><br>
John Ratliff has spoken well, continuosly, on this site. He was there to save lives.<br><br>
The politics of the war are one thing, but there is no denying the acts of heroism that made up every day events in Vietnam. Thanks for your service then, and your contributions to this website now.
